There you will find many helpful articles as well as "tips of the trade". Check it out. Expert Authority I guess you could call us the "Gurus" in specialty tires and tire chains. That's what we do ten hours a day every day. We've heard every question, every unusual application, every day, you name it. And we will take the extra step and search the US for your hard to find tires. Our customer service experts average 28 years experience in these markets. We sell to thousands of tire dealers, equipment companies, golf courses as well as the general public.

Description: Center for Economic and Policy Research promotes democratic debate on the most important economic and social issues.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: Center for Economic and Policy Research (CEPR) promotes democratic debate on the most important economic and social issues. The organization is committed to presenting issues in an accurate and understandable manner, so that the public is better prepared to choose among the various policy options. CEPR conducts both professional research and public education. The professional research is oriented towards filling important gaps in the understanding of particular economic and social problems, or the impact of specific policies. The public education portion of CEPR's mission is to present the findings of professional research, both by CEPR and others, in a manner that allows broad segments of the public to know exactly what is at stake in major policy debates. Center for Economic and Policy Research was established by Dean Baker and Mark Weisbrot in 1999 and is based in Washington, D.C.

Full Description: HouseLynxâ„¢ LLC delivers hardware and software for the residential home automation industry with home energy management being the first target application. HouseLynx has two customers.  1.) Retail Electric Providers (REP) in de-regulated energy markets need products and services that entice consumers to sign up with their service. HouseLynx enables REPâ€™s to bundle electricity with a tangible product and service (remote thermostat control).  This equates to longer, more profitable contracts and improves customer retention significantly. 2.) Consumers are frustrated with the lack of transparency and control they have with regards to their energy usage.
